            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> the vimscript bridge overhead can be expensive. It's worth considering adding a Lua version of this function and marking this as legacy.\n\nThose cases have Lua's stdlib and vim.uv though. After a good amount of discussion in chat, it's hard to justify adding new surface area for what will be nearly-duplicate interface to writefile().\n\nThe door is always open in the far future if we really want to, but meanwhile, it's better to make small, high-leverage changes that unblock the common case (as in the proposal here).",
